headline.main: ONE WEEK LATER FROM THE ISTHMUS.; Arrival of the St. Louis from Aspinwall. SAFE DISEMBARKATION OF U.S. TROOPS FOR CALIFORNIA. NEWS FROM THE SOUTH PACIFIC. GOLD DISCOVERIES IN CHILI. ANTICIPATED REVOLUTION IN PERU. TWELVE DAYS LATER FROM AUSTRALIA.

docs.lead_paragraph: The steamship St. Louis, A. C. CROOKER master,. from Aspinwall, N. G., consigned to Pacific Mail Steamship Company, arrived yesterday morning. She left New-York Dec. 11, 8:30 P. M. for Old Point Comfort, Va., arrived 5:30 P. M., 12th; sailed from Old Point 15th, 6 P. M., having on board the 9th Regiment Infantry, 800 officers and privates.

headline.main: BOARD OF COUNCILMEN.; Organization of the Board of Councilmen.
THE SNOW.; THE CITY IN WHITE ROBES. A Stormy Night on the Erie Railroad. The Carnival on Broadway--Many Streets Still Blockaded--The Ferries, &c.

CITY GOVERNMENT FOR 1856.; Organization of the Common Council. ANNUAL MESSAGE OF MAYOR WOOD. Mr. Wood's opiniens upon Governmental Policy. HEADS OF DEPARTMENTS SWORN IN. THE WHEELS ALL RUNNING SMOOTHLY.

docs.lead_paragraph: The new City Government was fully organized yesterday. Both the Boards of the Common Council were so unfashionable as to elect Presidents at once, making no sort of delay; and the Annual Message of Mayor WOOD was received and read. Business was cut out, ready to be operated upon, and then the City Fathers adjourned to their several homes with their laurels fresh upon them.
